description:
In this 50-pages long mini mag, Jasso has more wacky adventures!

NOTE: Jasso and his tale appeared in an anthology bofore this one, but the story isn`t reprinted to this.

The following stories are in Star Wars Black:

  1. Perfect Evil Part 1 by Hiromoto-SIN-Ichi
  2. Tantive IV by Formalin
  3. Evil Eyes by Nao
  4. Dear Anakin by Furi Furi Company

Also contains three illustrations by Kia Asamiya, Yuji Kaida, and Tsutomu Takahashi.
name: Black

person_credits.name: Dennis Worden
person_credits.role: writer, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

volume.name: Heckle and Jeckle the Talking Magpies Special!

deck: A warrior and healer living in a savage arid land, Noah is getting visions about the endless rain which will flood the Earth. People don't want to listen to his warnings, and Noah needs someone else's help to fulfill his mission...
name: Pour la cruautÃ© des hommes

deck: With the help of Giants, Noah has been building his Ark for many years. Now the Deluge is close, and tyrant Akkad gathers an army to capture the Ark and save his people...
name: Et tout ce qui rampe

description:
WIth EXCLUSIVE DIGITAL CONTENT including original art and sketches!

At last, a hint of what lies beneath the Weir. The secret of talking animals and dimensional portals - revealed!

Plus, one of our cast dies... and, we promise you, they will never return!
name: Here There Be Dragons

description: Yesterday, Walter tried to kill himself. Today, he wakes up to find that everyone who comes near him suddenly and inexplicably dies. Everyone, that is, except for a mysterious lady named Eliza, who is desperately trying to keep Walter safe from a deadly assassin known as Miller - which would be easy if he didn't keep coming back from the dead without a scratch on him. Learn the true meaning of life and death in AFFLICTION.
name: Chapter Two

description: Byron is nursed back to health by two beautiful women who are not what they seem. And when dinnertime rolls around, an uninvited guest yet AGAIN, saves the day.
I feel sorry for Gwen and the family. No notice, and now their boy is gone...

Winter has struck the old Ozarks, and Eve isnât prepared in the slightest. When her and Hieronymus do their darnedest to make it through the snowy season, they are interrupted by a gooey new monster of mysterious origins. And it might take more than walloping this beastie to make its distractions end!
Red's pursuit of fame goes to her head and it's up to the rest of the Fraggles to bring her back to reality.
Annie, Kat, and Shadow must try and save Robot after he's attacked and taken by a group of older robot models.
name: Changes

description: In issue 2 of Hawken, fan-favorite funk comic artist JIM MAHFOOD spins a club floor tale of excess Ego and revenge entitled "Friendly Fire", in which an ex-rock star turned mech pilot learns the hard way how dangerous his former partying ways can be to those around him... and himself!
name: Friendly Fire

description:
It's Back to School time for the Kiss Kids! The Kids try to navigate new school clothes, science fairs, and evil doppelganger robots, among other hurdles to rockin' all night and partyin' (after nap-time) all day...

Note: Some retailers received this issue early (10/2/2013) while the majority of retailers received it (10/9/2013).

From the Shuster award winning creators of Least I Could Do and Gutters comes a loving nod to classic fantasy novels that manages to flip the genre on it's head. Unlikely heros cut a swath through a fantasy world that is extremely familiar and yet very different. A naive elven hunter makes an strange friend in an undead warlock and the two manage to make both enemies and friends as they fight the good fight against the Legaran Empire.

Mickey Mouse is immersed in another diary inherited from his English ancestor Sir Mick de' Mouse! In this adventure, a trip to Damascus leads Mick de' Mouse to a unique artifact that seems to be linked to the ancient legend of Ali Baba...
name: Mickey Mouse and Ali Baba's Cave

description: Mickey Mouse opens the seventh diary describing another unbelievable adventure of his English relative Mick de' Mouse! It begins with a dangerous mission to the North Pole and the worrisome ambitions of the warlike state of Birania...
name: Mickey Mouse and Thor's Shield

description: In the eighth diary, Mickey Mouse reads about Mick de' Mouse's adventure in the Amazon forest, where the locals are really superstitious! Among the various legends, there's one about Piguazul, the god of the river, who seems have a serious problem with men...
name: The Piguazul Spirit

description: Almost being drowned and finding out a bunch of people you know might be superheroes is pretty rough. Sounds like everyone could use some tea, pizza, video games, and a sleepover. And probably some explanations. Some of those things are probably going to happen in this issue!

When the levee breaks, poor Max has to cross the borders of consciousness and dive into the abysmal birthday of his miserable city and self. While Max does the graveyard shift, a new uninvited player comes to town, ready to raise Hell. Now, who can change what is written in the stony pages of fate?

The harrowing conclusion to Miss Fury's race through time! Find out what happens to our hero and her roving gang of Roman soldiers. Can they defeat Harmon, or will they be stuck time-traveling forever? Part 6 of 6!

The infection spreads throughout the city as Jun and Shuang enact their escape, McCaw heads down a dark liquor-drenched road to hold on to what is his, Glitter's life hangs in the balance and Hong returns with unwelcome friends.
name: Season 03 (Part 1 of 2)

description: Noctua reminisces upon his past at Imago Labs as Svetlana begs him to tag along on his next hunt. Meanwhile, Crispus sends a strong-handed message to his contentious human subordinate while also meeting with a psychotic hitman. Back at headquarters, Agents Drake and Harker make a puzzling discovery regarding the DNA of the missing tooth found at the warehouse. All this and more as the saga continues, featuring the awe-inspiring debut of new artist J.C. Grande.
The murder of a scientist is causing more trouble for Solano than he thought it would.

Bridging the gap between Plastic Farm Part One (Sowing Seeds on Fertile Soil) and Plastic Farm Part Two (Seasons of Growth in the Fields of Despair), this 120 page masterpiece of a graphic novel is sure to wreck your brain and make you question your own place in the universe.

April, 1972. Living on a compound surrounded by those who have rejected the reality that modern society has imposed upon us all, Jonathan Picanos has begun to experiment with new forms of meditation and self-mutilation. His friends, while recognizing that Jonathan has become adept at his mastery over nature, do not realize the depths to which he has gone. When a new threat to their way of life emerges from the shadows, will Jonathan's mastery over reality save his friends and family, or will he lead them all to death and damnation?

April, 1998. Eliza Dorne is an assassin and, while she is quite good at her job, wishes to retire. She has completed what she hoped was her final mission, but her employer (a man known by many names, but most commonly known as The Reverend or The Smiling Man) is not so eager to let her go.

April, 1994. Frank and Benny were two honest cops killed while staking out the handoff of medical files between a junky and The Smiling Man. Now they find themselves resurrected and performing menial tasks as an undead zombie-like janitorial staff.

Three seemingly unrelated tales detailing three separate events that will reshape the lives and realities of all who dare enter the world of Plastic Farm.

Written by Rafer Roberts, with artwork by Wendi Strang-Frost and Jake Warrenfeltz.
name: Fertilizer, an interlude in three aprils

description:
This is the issue not to miss! A demon from the past appears to threaten Erin's sanity. Anne attempts to reach out to the life she once knew but can she get past the monster she's become? Meanwhile the main event that fans have been asking for since issue 1, Agent Simon and Suture face off and only one will walk away! As if that's not enough, the stage is set for the explosive finale as the mysterious puppeteer who has been pulling the strings is finally revealed!

Note: The digital edition (10/2/2013) for this issue was released a week before the print edition (10/9/2013)
The local color gets deeper as Sam Kimimura puts the pieces together. Also featuring an exclusive 8-page backup featuring art by Eric Kim!

So Buttons #4 written by Jonathan Baylis

Following in the Harvey Pekar model, Baylis partners with different artists to translate his stories into sequential art. The new issue contains artwork from Noah Van Sciver (Fantagraphics), Fred Hembeck (Marvel), Thomas Boatwright (Slave Labor Graphics), T.J. Kirsch (She Died in Terrebonne), and many others. So Buttons is an invitation to laugh and be moved by memories and experiences everyone can relate to.

A dark fantasy drama in a modern setting, Yumiko finds her perfect little life as the merch girl for her boyfriend's band going to Hell - literally. Yumi must help her friends realize they're caught in the middle of an ancient conflict between a god of excess and his jilted lover, before everyone dies as a result of it. This project redefines the possibilities of what comics can do when crossed with music, and is supported by an online animated music video.

volume.name: Yumiko: Curse of the Merch Girl

description: Pecos Bill finds out that in order to defeat Tempernado, he needs to accept who he is as a Tall Tale. Strapping on his jetpack, Pecos Bill races off to reclaim his identity in a fight that only one legend can survive. Meanwhile, a new threat enters the Hell's Gulch Gang.

Five years have passed since the Wolf Clan disbanded. The world has collapsed into complete and utter disorder. Cerberus, blamed for the Nord Catastrophe, now tries to earn redemption from his former Clansmen and himself as he attempts to set the world right. But can he do this all on his own?
name: Resist

description: Inspired by Marvel Comics' The Grapplers, This comic is the beginning of how a failing wrestling federation falls into the hands of a new ownership and how the hire of a new wrestler is going to change the face of wrestling history.
name: A New Beginning

person_credits.name: Joe D. McFee
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, production

description: In the first explosive issue the Vidulars - an ancient alien race decide to Hyper-Evolve a select amount of Earthlings in order to help in the fight with the Universal scourge - the Harmony. But not everybody is willing to fight. Meet characters like Epica, Brontosaurus and Heather Handgrenade in this Sci-Fi Superhero Epic of over 40 pages!

The next stage of evolution has laid dormant in our world just waiting for the proper spark... the right catalyst. From creators Joelle Selner, B. Alex Thompson, David Gorden, Lorenzo Lizana, and

Carl Reed comes the next evolution of heroes -- CATALYST: PRIME from LionForge Comics.
name: The Event

description:
Rusty McDoodle isn't having the best week. His web clients aren't paying, his girlfriend left him and his social skills have deteriorated from freelancing in a vacuum. His best friend Stan works in online porn, toiling away in a virtual sweat-shop lorded over by a maniacal boss and his dog-like cronies. When Stan's latest project goes up flames late one night, he asks Rusty to join the company and help him uncover the truth behind his Kafkaesque employer.

These two web-lackeys soon discover a series of events have been set in motion so bizarre, that their world is engulfed by epic chaos. With the help of an alcoholic psychic and his fishing buddy, they're roped into a nightmarish struggle with bloodthirsty demons and money-mongering yes-men. Can they keep their jobs and sanity intact when they can't trust anyone and there's an axe lurking behind every back?

Chicken Outfit is a sci-fi / horror comic for future-shocked times. It chronicles corporate greed, maniacal butchers, undead biker-chicks, drunken psychic shaman, pretentious aliens and a couple of under-paid slobs who find themselves in the most hellish situation of their lives.
name: The Maskman Cometh

description: When Donald Duck and Uncle Scrooge get trapped centuries in the past, it's up to Huey, Dewey, and Louie to save them. Well...to save Donald, that is. It seems that Uncle Scrooge has taken to piracy, and might not want to leave! Can the nephews rescue a waterlogged Donald and a power-crazed Uncle Scrooge from Davy Jones's locker?

volume.name: Donald Duck and the Niece of the Black Corsair

description: This DUST: WITHERED EARTH trade collects the complete DUST saga, previously released by Semantink Publishing and Keyleaf Comics - issues zero through six. DUST is the story of two travelers, Jim and Deborah, making their way through a post-apocalyptic world full of cannibals, mutants, pirates, mercenaries, and more, as they travel from Mexico to San Diego in an effort to change the harsh conditions of their reality.
name: TPB

description: See the collected life stories of Oprah, Barbara Walters, Ellen DeGeneres, and Meredith Vieira in this broad examination of strong women in the media.
name: TPB

volume.name: Female Force: Women In the Media

description:
Captain Gamma Lamar protects the citizens of the galaxy attached to the peacekeeping service, POLARIS. He and his friends travel though space dispensing justice and a side of humor.

In this first story, an isolated planet's water supply is cut off. Can Captain Lamar discover who is involved and keep the thirsty colony from drying up completely?

They framed her for the murder of the President, executed her husband in front of her, and nearly took the life of her infant son. Big mistake. Exiled from America, Danya Ben-El'azar and her six-year-old son Jonah have become the international mercenary team known only as The Golem. With sword and pistol, mother and son travel the world hunting the people who ruined their lives. THE GOLEM is a revenge tale set in a future where every moment of our lives is broadcast and privacy is a luxury. The haves and have-nots are physically divided with the upper class living in cities built in the sky while mechanized, heavily armed Spyders patrol the Lower City to keep the peace among the impoverished. Danya and son must navigate between these two worlds to find and destroy the men who betrayed them.
name: TPB

description: A collection of two related stories, "Holiday Phone Call" and "My Grandmother's Funeral." In "Holiday Phone Call," Mrs. Herrick receives a cold call that challenges her sense of reality. In "My Grandmother's Funeral," Mrs. Herrick has died and her granddaughter, Stephanie, has flown out to Iowa for the funeral. Yet in facing her grandmother's life, Stephanie must also face her own.
The streets of Brooklyn were as desolate as a ghost town. Or just about, for it wasn't always just zombies roaming the streets...

To make a choice is to take a risk, so Hinata simply coasts. When the older Kasahara pursues him, Hinata allows himself to fall into an awkward friendship. But Kasahara demands more and Hinata's hand is forced: will he take a risk and face his fears, or will he stay in his comfortable but empty life? Kozuki used to risk falling in love, but too much heartache has crushed his belief in "happily ever after," so he rejects his co-worker Sakashita's confession. However, Sakashita's love just won't fade. Will Kozuki take one more risk for love before it's too late? IF I TAKE YOUR HAND, what will happen?
name: Vol. 1

description: In the near future, Black Wave is the ultimate in interactive gaming. Its champion players are admired and celebrated. Now they are under attack by the "Ghost," a mystery murderer who might be player or program. The only thing they know for sure is that people are playing--and people are dying.
name: TPB

description: Izumi Etou is starting at a new school, Egret Academy, and he is excited to join the fencing club with his childhood friend, Yuuji Saeki. The reason he's so excited? Club President Takasaki, Izumi's handsome senpai, is there!! He dreams of becoming a graceful and strong man just like his senpai, but Izumi hates Vice President Ibe hanging all over Takasaki. Things becomeeven more complicated when Yuuji decides he's in love with Izumi, who's too engrossed with Takasaki to notice! Yuuji isn't straightforward with his feelings, so how can he make Izumi return them? Who will be Izumi's love in the end?
name: Vol. 1

description:
Following a devastating psychic terror attack The Old King of Albion lies on his death bed lamenting his failures.

He calls for his son; the young Prince Jonathan of the Rose, to put right what he once put wrong... Who will save the Kingdom?

Is it finally time for The Lion and The Unicorn to return!

A Top Shelf digital exclusive!

Can you believe it - over 300 pages of Lizz Lunney! This massive collection includes early comics, recent comics, all your favorite characters, and even a dash of autobiography! Join Lizz as she takes cartoon comedy to the limit, featuring cute cubes, specks of dust, talkative foods, and most importantly, plenty of cats. 314 pages!
name: TPB

description: Showcasing the gorgeous good-girl pin-up art of Omar Dogan, Girl Seven features a cast of seven lovely ladies, all designed by Omar Dogan in a variety of themes such as swimsuits, martial arts, sports, goth, uniforms, and more. Over 80 all-new, full-color pin-ups have been created exclusively for this volume, plus rough sketches, character profiles, and creator commentary throughout the book.
When Wendell is dared by bullies to stay overnight in an abandoned, burned down Renaissance Fair, he meets a man dressed as a knight who believes that the fire was caused by a dragon.
name: Wendell In the Woods

description: Forced to carve out a hardscrabble existence on an unforgiving colony planet, the citizens of Hillsborough Township have awakened something sinister in the mines outside of town... creatures. Their only hope lies with Angus Shepperton, town drunk and no-good husband. Shepperton embarks on a quest to save the souls of the townsfolk that never passed up a chance to kick him when he was down. However, his last chance for redemption depends on his ability to indulge his greatest weakness. This sci-fi creature western is graphic novel by Oort Cloud Comics.
name: GN

description: A lone astronaut in space, orbiting the earth after a nuclear war, a night on the town goes bad, killer robots from the future sent back in time to destroy humanity, and two tales of revenge served cold -- welcome to Shorts + Losses.

Trouble arises when Norio encounters a legendary gang of thieves. Pushing his skills to the limit, the showdown forces him to alter his technique, creating a new style of fighting for the Old West. Get ready for the bullets to fly, and the heads to roll!

There's no peace on Earth when Christmas comes to the Smurfs Village, at least not while Gargamel is lurking about! In this special collection of frosty fun and frolic, before The Smurfs can stuff their stockings and open their presents, they have to deal with dragons, talking snowmen, grumpy bears, a kidnapped Santa Claus, and a reindeer chase through the starry night sky! It's a race to save Christmas in this Smurfy Holiday treasure for the whole family.

Note: The digital edition (10/2/2013) for this special was released before the print edition (10/30/2013).

Story Titles

  • Little Peter's Christmas
  • The Ogre and the Smurfs
  • Strange Snowmen
  • The Little Tree
  • The Smurfs Christmas
name: GN

description: A group of survivors stumble around a post nuclear holocaust London as the Angel of Death ponders their Stiff Upper Lip attitude.
Join our hero, Toaster Guy, as he embarks on a life of fighting crime in all its macabre forms - a life he didn't ask for!

volume.name: The Strange Adventures of Toaster Guy

description: Prologue: Meet Ronnie Van Helsing, Agent of the multi-national anti-vampire spy organization the Polidorium, as she scales a mountain in Colorado in search of a creature hidden in a frozen vault.

Humanity's last colony has exiled themselves to a small valley where all forms of advance technology have been outlawed. A traveling magician named Merrick uses black market tech to trick the local villagers into thinking he's using real magic, but when a visitor from the skies crashes down everything he ever thought was real is finally revealed.
name: OGN

description: Presenting all the TRANSFORMERS covers from the Robots in Disguise complete run of comics! This oversize hardcover features the art that your childhood memories are made of by such luminaries as Bill Sienkiewicz, Michael Golden, Mark Bright, Herb Trimpe, Don Perlin, Bob Budiansky, Tom Morgan, Jose Delbo, Pat Lee, Don Figueroa, James Raiz, Guido Guidi, EJ Su, Alex Milne, Ashley Wood, and others!
The story of an anarchist prophet set in a dystopian future where humans are ruled by a technological deity.
name: GN

person_credits.name: Stevyn Llewellyn
person_credits.role: writer, artist, penciler, inker, colorist, cover

description: What happens when supervillains become mere criminals? Nancy Grace and Simon Van Zandt got out of the cape-game a few years ago. They were tired of the mad plans and getting their heads kicked in by a bunch of do-gooders. But when their old boss, the Duchess comes back and tells them they can still do jobs, they just can't wear the costumes, the money starts rolling in and times are good. The only problem? Nancy and Simon miss the masks more than they ever thought...

After a long secret war, The Illuminati won.

They lifted the barrier and supernatural forces were among us again.

We lost, darkness engulfed the world. But then... things went back to normal, sort of.

Humans left sane now cry black tears, but are otherwise ok. You know, as much as you could be.

Creatures from evil places took the jobs, leaving lesser monsters and humans to... Doss around down the pub.

Jan Czernowicz took this world to heart, learning dark arts from his best friend Shugg, rebellious spawn of an Elder council beast-lord.

He does odd sorcery jobs between stints of sod all, around the Vale of Aylesbury.
name: Council State

description: Redneck, trailer trash, drug-running vampires, bounty-hunting biker werewolves, immortal desperadoes, an ancient mummy hitman and the Egyptian Mafia: these are the kinds of perpetrators that covert U.S. Marshal Wynonna Earp hunts down on a regular basis. Created by writer Beau Smith, Wynonna Earp is the descendant of the famous lawman Wyatt Earp. As a member of the so-called "Halloween Hunters" or "Freak Finders," she does what comes supernatural... she brings the unnatural to justice. If there's a monster committing crime in your neighborhood, then she'll be there to bag and tag 'em. His legend. Her legacy. their law. Wynonna Earp is a quirky, head-busting mixture of action/adventure/sci-fi/dark humor.
name: TPB

description: Redneck, trailer trash, drug-running vampires, bounty-hunting biker werewolves, immortal desperadoes, an ancient mummy hitman and the Egyptian Mafia: these are the kinds of perpetrators that covert U.S. Marshal Wynonna Earp hunts down on a regular basis. Created by writer Beau Smith, Wynonna Earp is the descendant of the famous lawman Wyatt Earp. As a member of the so-called "Halloween Hunters" or "Freak Finders," she does what comes supernatural... she brings the unnatural to justice. If there's a monster committing crime in your neighborhood, then she'll be there to bag and tag 'em. His legend. Her legacy. their law. Wynonna Earp is a quirky, head-busting mixture of action/adventure/sci-fi/dark humor.
name: TPB
In der Falle der Pistoleros ; Der teuflische Plan

volume.name: Firefighter! Daigo of Fire Company M
Happy Birthday! (And One to Glow On!)

description: Previously only available in graphic novel longform, in this first issue of Joe Daly's popular 'Dungeon Quest' Millennium Boy decided to grab his hobo stick, his bandanna, and his Swiss Army knife, bid his mom goodbye, and head off on a quest. Joined by his best friend Steve (weapon: baseball bat; clothing: wife beater, cargo pants and sandals), the two sort out a few of the details their adventure.

The second issue of Joe Daly's Dungeon Quest, previously only available in graphic novel longform! Millennium Boy decided to grab his hobo stick, his bandanna, and his Swiss Army knife, bid his mom goodbye, and head off on a quest. Joined by his best friend Steve (weapon: baseball bat; clothing: wife beater, cargo pants and sandals), the two sort out a few of the details their adventure.

Previously only available in graphic novel longform, in this first issue of Joe Daly's popular 'Dungeon Quest' Millennium Boy decided to grab his hobo stick, his bandanna, and his Swiss Army knife, bid his mom goodbye, and head off on a quest. Joined by his best friend Steve (weapon: baseball bat; clothing: wife beater, cargo pants and sandals), the two sort out a few of the details their adventure.

From defending the U.S. Navy from the Barbary Pirates, the United States Marines are first on the scene and the last to leave. In AMERICAN DEFENDERS: THE UNITED STATES MARINES, we find out how the few, the proud and the brave not only fight for freedom, but continue to defend America in their greatest times in need whether it be in the Halls of Montezuma or on the shores of Tripoli, you will be amazed their courage, tenacity and bravery.

Last issue! The final chapter reaches its horrific conclusion as the surviving team members at long last reach their destination, only to face threats from within and without their ranks. The fate of Ian's fiancÃ©e Jen and the bunker staff is revealed, but will Ian live long enough to find them?

Lucy administers all kinds of advice, psychiatric and otherwise in the first part of this two-part collection of strips cataloguing all of the PEANUTS neighborhood neuroses. The doctor is in â five cents please!
name: Volume Two

description: The underdog San Francisco Flying Aces team as they go toe-to-toe against New York's undefeated East Side Homewreckers. We meet two of the arch rivals who will appear in subsequent issues.
name: Homewreckers vs. Flying Aces

description: "Kamikaze" Fey Sankawa, who moves like a samurai through her city life - headstrong, bound and determined to carve her own path. The only girl in the dockyards, she drives a forklift and wrangles cargo off the ships in San Francisco Bay. Despite her mother's protestations, she refuses to quit and return to Hokkaido, but soon catches the eye of former child actor Hamilton Scofield, who invites her to tryout for his underdog roller derby team. She brings the grit, but will she have what it takes to become one of The Flying Aces?
name: Kamikaze

description: The world of bad girl Carmen Elisabeta Consuelos y MartÃ­nez, best known as "Lizard Brain", last year's Most Valuable Player and all-star powerhouse. In 2030, once again she prepares to jam for her team, the formidable East Side Homewreckers, as they vie for the national league trophy.From the dusty Mexican border to the streets of Brooklyn, Lizard delivers a bevy of bone-crushing moves to keep her rivals at bay. Off the track, she's also passionate about her boyfriend, Viper, though his shady business deals bring unexpected dangers. Out of the underworld and into the high life, will reigning queen Lizard Brain keep her crown?
name: Lizard Brain

description: When Kamikaze suits up for her first bout with the Flying Aces, her debut doesn't go entirely as expected â and neither does the after-party. PLUS: Get a first glimpse of Maglev Madness, the new technology that raises derby to new heights!
name: Kamizake Takes Off

description: Roller derby evolves with Maglev Madness. Through technological advances the players fly around a frictionless track at breakneck speeds, Â­Â­requiring quick reflexes and nerves of steel. Maglev Skates provide levitation by repelling from an array of electromagnets embedded in the track. Processor-controlled sensors adjust the polarity of the magnets and propel the skater according to player stance, play conditions and safety regulations. Jammers vie to outrun each other in sprint races up to 100 miles per hour. Join San Francisco's Flying Aces â including Kamikaze, Dinah Might and Mortal Cindy â as they take on the favorite Los Angeles Lightning. Can the underdogs find their way to glory?
name: California Fast Track

description: Everyone's a hero in Homeland! Occupy your mind with comics on the political satirical front, including Barcourt's Mother, Comfort Creatures and Tea-Party Tom! Meet some of the characters you'll encounter: In "Barcourt's Mother": Barcourt's Mother -- A Puritan lady born in 1632, now facing the rigors of life in this modern age of sin and corruption. She drives a curved dash Olds and isn't afraid to spoil the rod to spare the child! Barcourt -- Her wily son, fun loving and naive, haplessly wanders into situations that threaten to bring shame and abomination on his mother and the church. Dwayne the Hippie -- The ne'er-do-well rabble rouser who regularly leads Barcourt astray.

Homeland #2 VOTE TO WIN! : The 2012 Presidential Election Issue Wham! Bam! Comics strikes again with another issue of "Homeland", just in time for the 2012 Presidential race! In the second issue, revisit the Comfort Creatures gang as perennial temp Arty Mocker ponders how to cast his vote; Barcourt's Mother drives her son to the Washington -- the 'Gomorrah by the Pacific' -- on a pilgrimage for his political enlightenment; and we get an insider's glimpse of the world's wealthiest in "Name Your Wage" and "Superheroes for the One-Percent!"
Contains : X-Men (2013) #03
Contains : All-New X-Men (2013) #14
"Hell's Bells" part 1 of 4! Batman's latest altercation with the Gotham City Police Department forces him to improvise, when they converge on a suspect-and the police try to take HIM out instead!
name: Hell's Bells, Part 1 of 4

description:
An 'Avengers vs X-Men' chapter! Thor confronts the Phoenix! Captain America versus Gambit! Spidey tackles Colossus!

By Brian Michael Bendis, Walt Simonson, Kieron Gillen and Steve McNiven

Featuring material first published in Avengers #25-26 and AVX #2.
